               <p>GEORGE POTTS. I am a <rs id="t18271206-113-viclabel590" type="occupation">sailor</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271206-113-victim684 t18271206-113-viclabel590"></join> on board the Earl of Talbot, of London. On the 28th of October she was in the river, off the <placeName id="t18271206-113-crimeloc591">Hermitage-stairs</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18271206-113-crimeloc591" type="placeName" value="Hermitage-stairs"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18271206-113-crimeloc591" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271206-113-off588 t18271206-113-crimeloc591"></join>; the prisoner was a stranger, but had been on board about ten days, assisting the men to discharge a cargo of bark and timber; he asked me that day if I would let him lay in the cabin - I had the care of the vessel, and gave him leave: I kept my clothes in master's state-room, which is near the cabin: next morning I saw the cabin lamp laying by the windlass - I then missed my clothes from my chest. The prisoner was then gone - I did not see him again for about sixteen days.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18271206-113-person685">
